                            <comment id="14478430" author="pniederw" created="Wed, 21 Jan 2009 05:27:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Are you aware that you are passing in a list? Both of the following work fine for me:&lt;br/&gt;
foo(1, &quot;B&quot;, 0.5)&lt;br/&gt;
foo(*&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1, &amp;quot;B&amp;quot;, 0.5&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;) // spread operator&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Conversely, foo([ 1, &quot;B&quot;, 0.5 ]) doesn&apos;t work for me no matter which of your method definitions I use. And I&apos;d be surprised if it did.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466268" author="blackdrag" created="Wed, 21 Jan 2009 06:19:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;in fact there is a special method invocation path for this. So I think it should work... I very dislike that path btw. I prefer the usage of the spread operator&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466386" author="roshandawrani" created="Fri, 23 Jan 2009 13:25:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed on 1.5.8 and 1.7-beta-1. When the 1.6.1 branch is setup, I will fix it there.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466436" author="roshandawrani" created="Thu, 29 Jan 2009 18:56:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed on 1.6.1 too. Overall fixed on 1.5.8 / 1.6.1 / 1.7-beta-1 branches.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
